aes::semantic(self_ref_in_relation)

  × self-reference not allowed in `let` body
   ╭─[test.aes:2:16]
 1 │ type user {
 2 │   let owner = .owner;
   ·                ──┬──
   ·                  ╰── `.relation` syntax is not valid here
 3 │ }
   ╰────
  help: `let` defines what external types can be stored as subjects — use `def` for permissions that reference the type's own relations
